rComments: Dr. Safran is an exacting professor, she demands and expects the best from her students. Her lectures are clear & well organized. I did miserably in her course but I thank her no end for giving me a dose of what graduate school will be like. I am sorry I had to be one of her bad students, a tad harsh on criticism but a good professor nonetheless.

Prof. Safran is amazingly well-read and helpful.  She is exacting and challenging, which some people might find intimidating, but if you are open to her help, you will be very pleased with what she can help you achieve (and you will discover that she is very sweet!).
